Key Match Events: Kalinauskas scored the only goal for Lithuania in the 68th minute
Pre-Game Insights: Lithuania boss Edgaras Jankauskas has made the brave decision of leaving out his two most experienced players for their two matches this month
Cyprus manager Temuri Ketsbaia is under increasing pressure in the away dugout
Post-Match Reflections: Lithuania had their struggles in the last Nations League campaign, but made up for it with some impressive results in Euro 2024 qualification, and should come into this break slightly rejuvenated after recent wins over Gibraltar, and only a narrow defeat in the Baltic Cup
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cyprus won their last international fixture, but that was to be expected against San Marino
Cyprus have failed to win a competitive away match since 2019 against Kazakhstan - losing 14 of the 17 since
Others: Lithuania possible starting lineup: Gertmonas; Lekiatas, Kazukolovas, Tutyskinas; Lasickas, Slivka, Verbickas, Vorobjovas, Sirvys; Kucys, Paulauskas
Cyprus possible starting lineup: Mall; Kyprianou, Gogic, Laifis; Andreou, Charalampous, Kyriakou, Anderson Correia; Pittas, Kastanos, Loizou
